Universal Pictures has landed the project, with Theron also in talks to produce. The thriller will tell the story of a wife and mother who works as a CIA analyst.One day while digitally searching files in hopes of unmasking a Russian sleeper cell in the US, she makes a shocking discovery that not only threatens her job, but also her family and her life.Writer Cleveland herself worked as an analyst for the CIA, with the book causing a buzz late last week with several studios making offers, although it hasn't officially been set for publishing.Oscar-winner Theron can soon be seen in action movie The Fate Of The Furious and most recently wrapped production on Tully.